<div id="review_334518476" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/334518476" />
    <a title="Stacia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/349714-stacia"><img alt="Stacia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546969803p2/349714.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/334518476?book_show_action=true">May 22, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stacia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stacia" href="/user/show/349714-stacia">Stacia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/349714-stacia?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/349714-stacia?shelf=2012">2012</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer334518476" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11227531749299054233">I loved the predecessor to this book, Sister of My Heart. It was a fabulous story of strong women. They made amazing selfless choices out of love and loyalty to each other. Even when you didn&apos;t agree with their actions, you understood their motivations clearly. I highly recommend Sister of My Heart.<br/><br/>I was excited to find out a sequel existed and picked up The Vine Of Desire almost immediately. Somehow, this book was the opposite of the first and made me dislike almost all of the characters I love</span>
  <span id="freeText11227531749299054233" style="display:none">I loved the predecessor to this book, Sister of My Heart. It was a fabulous story of strong women. They made amazing selfless choices out of love and loyalty to each other. Even when you didn't agree with their actions, you understood their motivations clearly. I highly recommend Sister of My Heart.<br /><br />I was excited to find out a sequel existed and picked up The Vine Of Desire almost immediately. Somehow, this book was the opposite of the first and made me dislike almost all of the characters I loved so much before. The characters acted very selfishly on all fronts and their motivations were almost a complete mystery. I think the intent was to explore freedom from duty and putting yourself first but everyone was hurtful and self-absorbed. <br /><br />It ended better than I expected but I still didn't enjoy this book and wish I had stopped after the first.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11227531749299054233" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


