    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_26894844" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/26894844" />
    <a title="Dee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1309554-dee"><img alt="Dee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1215537485p2/1309554.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/26894844?book_show_action=true">Jul 10, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dee" href="/user/show/1309554-dee">Dee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer26894844" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2642778949985796664">I would read another novel by this author but this wasn&apos;t a favorite by any means. The author&apos;s wonderful rich &amp; layer discriptive details are lost in the first 100 pages. It took me that long to truly get into the meat of the novel. There are short &amp; strange movie/storie plot lines told in a Bollywood type manner which seem surreal &amp; don&apos;t really add to the story. I was glad when the main character finally triumphed but felt like it took forever to read this book. </span>
  <span id="freeText2642778949985796664" style="display:none">I would read another novel by this author but this wasn't a favorite by any means. The author's wonderful rich &amp; layer discriptive details are lost in the first 100 pages. It took me that long to truly get into the meat of the novel. There are short &amp; strange movie/storie plot lines told in a Bollywood type manner which seem surreal &amp; don't really add to the story. I was glad when the main character finally triumphed but felt like it took forever to read this book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2642778949985796664" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


