<div id="review_1363349755" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1363349755" />
    <a title="Nico" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25268331-nico"><img alt="Nico" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1430077996p2/25268331.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1363349755?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nico" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nico" href="/user/show/25268331-nico">Nico</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1363349755" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7164632281907049449">I enjoyed this book, but not as much as the first &quot;Sister of My Heart&quot;. I love the writing style and imagery. I&apos;m not sure why, but at the end of the book I just felt very sad although, everyone&apos;s life was simply going on after new learning experiences. I might sound a little lazy in saying this, but I wish the author would have a glossary of terms. There were a lot of Indian terms that I didn&apos;t know, it just would have been helpful, considering the book was written in English - apparently for a</span>
  <span id="freeText7164632281907049449" style="display:none">I enjoyed this book, but not as much as the first "Sister of My Heart". I love the writing style and imagery. I'm not sure why, but at the end of the book I just felt very sad although, everyone's life was simply going on after new learning experiences. I might sound a little lazy in saying this, but I wish the author would have a glossary of terms. There were a lot of Indian terms that I didn't know, it just would have been helpful, considering the book was written in English - apparently for an English speaking audience. Unless one is very familiar with Indian foods, plants, and clothing it's a little bit of a challenge.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7164632281907049449" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


