<div id="review_1939178396" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1939178396" />
    <a title="Sunita Rajwade" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2391018-sunita-rajwade"><img alt="Sunita Rajwade" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1570771989p2/2391018.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1939178396?book_show_action=true">Mar 11, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sunita Rajwade" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sunita Rajwade" href="/user/show/2391018-sunita-rajwade">Sunita Rajwade</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2391018-sunita-rajwade?shelf=reading-challenge-2017">reading-challenge-2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1939178396" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10363168287080024253">I was expecting Chitra Banerjee&apos;s book to be magical but I think after the very first book I&apos;ve read, her stories have been a bit disappointing. Sticking to the formula of two sisters who are soul searching, the story does have an unexpected ending.<br/>Anju a young wife in California calls Sudha her rebel sister with a young daughter to come and be with her while she nurses a the grief of the loss of her unborn son. But this action is not without its consequences and predictably, creates another con</span>
  <span id="freeText10363168287080024253" style="display:none">I was expecting Chitra Banerjee's book to be magical but I think after the very first book I've read, her stories have been a bit disappointing. Sticking to the formula of two sisters who are soul searching, the story does have an unexpected ending.<br />Anju a young wife in California calls Sudha her rebel sister with a young daughter to come and be with her while she nurses a the grief of the loss of her unborn son. But this action is not without its consequences and predictably, creates another conflict in her life. It soon becomes apparent that the mousy Sudha has a side to her that no one knew of. Equally Anju uses this opportunity to make a go of her life after the loss of her child. <br />In typical lyrical prose, Divakarui's book captivates you but at times I found it too fanciful and at times too slow. However, the characters are well fleshed out and even though I wasn't hooked from the first word, I didn't find it too tedious a read.<br />Not exactly a light read, but not very thought provoking either. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10363168287080024253" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


